software development
fields.depiction: Projects centered on building, purchasing, and deploying software solutions to support business operations, customer needs, and internal user productivity. Can include custom mobile/web/desktop application development, integration between systems, implementation of third-party software packages, legacy modernization, and application upgrades.

fields.name: collaboration/productivity
fields.depiction: Implementing new systems and tools for communication, collaboration, content/document management, scheduling, and project management. This improves workforce connectivity, alignment, and productivity. Example projects: enterprise social networks, instant messaging, Office 365 deployment, SharePoint portals, project management systems.

fields.name: Customer mobile account management application development
fields.depiction: This project focuses on building a new customer-facing mobile app that allows users to access their account, get account balances, make payments, and manage account preferences anytime from their mobile device. The scope includes developing the front-end mobile application for both iOS and Android platforms, integrating with back-end account management systems via APIs, building a responsive web version for accessibility, ensuring security controls are designed into the application, load testing and performance tuning, and releasing a production version for download in the app stores after thorough quality assurance testing. Post-launch, the app will be enhanced over time to add new capabilities based on customer feedback and usage analytics. The goal is to provide customers a convenient, user-friendly, and secure way to manage their account on-the-go and resolve common service needs without calling the contact center.

fields.name: Unified communications platform implementation
fields.depiction: This project will implement a new Unified Communications platform consisting of instant messaging, voice, video conferencing, and screen sharing capabilities. It will replace the current fragmented collaboration tools with a single integrated platform to improve workforce connectivity and collaboration. The project will roll out the new UC software across the organization, migrate users from legacy systems, integrate the software with Active Directory for authentication, implement audio/video equipment in conference rooms, train employees on new conferencing and collaboration features, and establish governance policies around usage. Once fully deployed, the UC platform aims to increase workforce productivity by streamlining communication channels, facilitating remote meetings, and enabling collaboration across dispersed teams and offices. Adoption will be measured through usage analytics and surveys. Ongoing maintenance and user support will be provided by the IT service desk.

fields.name: bug
fields.depiction: Software bugs are problems in the design, building, or use of computer programs that lead to incorrect or surprising results. The process of identifying and fixing these issues is called debugging. Debugging often uses formal methods or tools to pinpoint the exact causes of bugs. Since the middle of the last century, some computer systems have included features to forestall, detect, or automatically fix various bugs while the software is running. The overall meaning remains the same - software bugs are errors that need to be found and corrected, and debugging is an important part of software development and maintenance.

fields.name: maintenance
fields.depiction: Maintenance tasks involve the ongoing activities necessary to keep systems, equipment, or infrastructure in proper working condition. This can include routine inspections, repairs, updates, and replacements of components to prevent deterioration or malfunctions. Maintenance tasks are essential to extend the lifespan and ensure the continued reliability of assets, reducing the likelihood of unexpected failures and downtime.

fields.name: enhancement
fields.depiction: Enhancement refers to a substantial improvement or service offering that includes significant supplemental capabilities, as concluded exclusively on the corporate level and as designated in an Order Form.

fields.name: UI login page error troubleshooting
fields.depiction: Investigate and fix the bug where users are unable to log in due to a JavaScript error on the login page. This involves identifying the root cause, modifying the code to resolve the issue, and thoroughly testing to ensure the problem is completely resolved and users can log in seamlessly.

fields.name: Apply security patches
fields.depiction: Regularly update and maintain the system by applying security patches, addressing vulnerabilities, and ensuring the software's security. This task focuses on identifying and patching vulnerabilities that could potentially be exploited, keeping the system secure and up to date.

fields.name: Improve the website's search functionality
fields.depiction: The goal of this task is to improve the website's search functionality in order to provide more relevant results for users. This will involve implementing partial word matching and synonym support within the search algorithm to expand the capabilities beyond exact keyword searches. Additional efforts will focus on optimizing the search index to incorporate new site content, adding filter/faceted search by attributes like product category and date, and improving the ranking of results by analyzing word frequency. Other planned enhancements are expanding search to include related documents and media, adding autocomplete suggestions and search keywords in the results page UI, implementing search usage tracking to guide future optimizations, and performing thorough search quality testing to measure improvements in relevance. Overall, this enhancement encompasses upgrades to the core search algorithm, index, UI, and analytics to make search on the website more powerful and effective for finding relevant content.
